<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="assume-vt">assume <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ə'sjuːm/    美 /ə'suːm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-take">1.<strong>[正式用语] 担任；承担 (take)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>assume office
就职</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I made a mistake and I will <strong>assume responsibility for</strong> it. 
我错了，我愿意为此承担责任。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>假定；设想</strong></h4>
<p>to accept or think that sth is true although you have no proof：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We think <strong>it is reasonable to assume</strong> they lived in these caves, regardless of the cold. 
我们认为，假设他们不顾严寒住在这些洞穴里是有道理的。</p><footer>人教⑧ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It is</strong> generally <strong>assumed</strong> (<strong>that</strong>) stress is caused by too much work.
普遍认为，压力系工作过重所致。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Where unemployment and crime are high, it can <strong>be assumed that</strong> the latter is due to the former.
在失业率和犯罪率高的地方，我们可以假定高犯罪率是由高失业率造成的。</p><footer>2009 江苏</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>assuming [ə'suːmɪŋ] conj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Assuming (that) you’re chosen to be the leader, what will you do?
假设你被选为领导，你会怎么做？</p></div></div>